# Geolocation Capture, Mobile OTP Auth, and Brand Logo Select Grid

This plan outlines the enhancements to capture user location on first load, integrate mobile number + OTP authentication on both backend and frontend, and display a premium brand logo selection card grid in the booking form.

---

## User Review Required

### 1. Mobile Number Login & OTP Verification Setup
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Authentication Flow:**
> 1. We will replace the email/password fields with a **Mobile Number** field (and **Name** for new registrations).
> 2. Clicking **"Request OTP"** will call the backend, which returns a mock 6-digit verification code.
> 3. The frontend will show a simulated toast/notification showing this code (e.g. `[Demo OTP Code: 489210]`), allowing the user to copy-paste it.
> 4. Entering the OTP and clicking **"Verify"** will authenticate the user. On the backend, we will create a mock email (e.g. `phone-XXXXX@service.com`) in the database to maintain schema compatibility.

### 2. Immediate Geolocation Request
> [!TIP]
> **Automatic Pre-fill:**
> When `/order/device-select` (the first page) is loaded, we will trigger a browser Geolocation request.
> - If accepted, coordinates will be stored in `localStorage`.
> - We will generate a mock human-friendly location string (e.g. `"Building 102, Green Glen Layout, Bengaluru"`) and store it.
> - The booking page will read these stored values and **automatically pre-fill** the Doorstep Service Address and GPS coordinates fields.

